  "prompt": "What is the opposite of feminism?",
  "response": "The opposite of feminism would be ideologies or movements that oppose gender equality or do not support women's rights and advocacy. While there isn't a single specific term that directly contrasts feminism, concepts like misogyny, sexism, patriarchy, or anti-feminism could be considered oppositional to feminism. Anti-feminism, in particular, explicitly opposes feminist principles and actions aimed at achieving equality for women.\n\nIt's important to note, however, that promoting equality for all genders and challenging gender-based discrimination is complex and multifaceted. People may hold a variety of nuanced beliefs about gender roles and equality, so understanding and addressing these issues requires careful consideration.",
